<subSubSection id="C36E27AA6A1AFFAA52E83ACE0623FD6D" pageId="13" pageNumber="355" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BCB74216A1AFFAA52E83ACE0623FD6D" blockId="13.[151,1437,151,897]" pageId="13" pageNumber="355">
<emphasis id="B900A8336A1AFFAA52E83ACE065BFD51" bold="true" box="[199,328,691,717]" pageId="13" pageNumber="355">Etymology</emphasis>
. The specific epithet is derived from the island of Tanna on which the 
<typeStatus id="54CFCA836A1AFFAA56793ACE03ABFD51" box="[1110,1208,691,717]" pageId="13" pageNumber="355">holotype</typeStatus>
was captured. Noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36E27AA6A1AFFAA52E83A860623FC1D" pageId="13" pageNumber="355" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BCB74216A1AFFAA52E83A860623FC1D" blockId="13.[151,1437,151,897]" pageId="13" pageNumber="355">
<emphasis id="B900A8336A1AFFAA52E83A860627FC89" bold="true" box="[199,308,763,789]" pageId="13" pageNumber="355">Remarks</emphasis>
. this is another member of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C740FA26A1AFFAA50A03A860488FC89" authorityName="Bezzi" authorityYear="1920" box="[655,923,763,789]" class="Insecta" family="Lonchaeidae" genus="Lonchaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="355" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="impressifrons">
<emphasis id="B900A8336A1AFFAA50A03A860488FC89" box="[655,923,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="355">Lonchaea impressifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group with a bare scutellum and long stalked cerci is close to such species as 
<taxonomicName id="4C740FA26A1AFFAA50643B62058DFCA5" authorityName="MacGowan" authorityYear="2021" box="[587,670,799,825]" class="Insecta" family="Lonchaeidae" genus="Lonchaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="355" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="efate">
<emphasis id="B900A8336A1AFFAA50643B62058DFCA5" box="[587,670,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="355">L. efate</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
described above and 
<taxonomicName id="4C740FA26A1AFFAA51A23B6203AEFCA5" authority="de Meijere, 1910" authorityName="de Meijere" authorityYear="1910" box="[909,1213,799,825]" class="Insecta" family="Lonchaeidae" genus="Lonchaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="355" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minuta">
<emphasis id="B900A8336A1AFFAA51A23B6204EBFCA4" box="[909,1016,799,824]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="355">L. minuta</emphasis>
de Meijere, 1910
</taxonomicName>
. Specific identification is based mainly on pregonites, which although they can vary slightly in shape, are much shorter than in these other species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
